reviewText: The kettles were shown at the movies when I was a little girl and I have seen them all.  Still love them and have purchased all of them twice from Amazon as I gave one set to my daughter-in-law. Decent to watch with the family, no sex, no blasphemy, no cursing.  Even though Pa kettle was lazy, he was honest.  I gave them five stars but would gladly have given them a ten if that was an option.
Title: Further Adventures of the Kettles Collection

reviewText: I am fan of the "Kettle" movies and own the first eight movies released on earlier DVDs. When I ran across these additional Kettle movies I wanted them to complete my collection. But in these two movies Percy Kilbride, the original Pa Kettle is absent and the children are different. The producers attempted to work around Pa being absent and the original children aging out, but the movies just don't have the same chemistry as before. I will keep the movies, but they aren't the best of the Kettle series.
Title: Further Adventures of the Kettles Collection
